Definition.WordDefinition:
toto
<programming> /toh-toh'/ The default scratch file name among French-speaking programmers - in other words, a francophone {foo}. The phonetic mutations "titi", "tata", and "tutu" canonically follow "toto", analogously to {bar}, {baz} and {quux} in English.
[{Jargon File}]
